Package: LibeRality
Type: Package
Title: Model-Informed Optimal Clinical Trial Design
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Sven C.", "van Dijkman",
    email = "svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Sven C. van Dijkman [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Sven C. van Dijkman <svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: Model-informed evaluation, optimisation, robustness analysis, and
    simulation of clinical trial designs for nonlinear mixed-effects
    pharmacokinetic and pharmacodynamic models. Reuses LibeRation model and
    event specifications, obtains exact prediction sensitivities from
    LibeRtAD-backed C++ engines, and supports continuous, categorical, count,
    ordinal, and time-to-event outcomes. Implements local, Bayesian, robust,
    discrimination, power, prediction, clinical-decision, cost, burden,
    compound, constrained, and Pareto design criteria with continuous,
    discrete, integer, allocation, and hybrid optimisation. This research and
    teaching software does not replace protocol review, statistical review,
    ethics review, or clinical judgement.
